verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto all the congregation of the children of Israel, and say unto them, Ye shall be holy: for I the Lord your God am holy.
verses.verse_html: 2Speak unto all the congregation of the children of Israel, and say unto them, Ye shall be holy: for I the Lord your God am holy.

tokens.text: unto them, Ye shall be holy

verses.text_plain: Ye shall fear every man his mother, and his father, and keep my sabbaths: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 3Ye shall fear every man his mother, and his father, and keep my sabbaths: I am the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: Turn ye not unto idols, nor make to yourselves molten gods: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 4Turn ye not unto idols, nor make to yourselves molten gods: I am the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: And if ye offer a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the Lord, ye shall offer it at your own will.
verses.verse_html: 5And if ye offer a sacrifice of peace offerings unto the Lord, ye shall offer it at your own will.

verses.text_plain: It shall be eaten the same day ye offer it, and on the morrow: and if ought remain until the third day, it shall be burnt in the fire.
verses.verse_html: 6It shall be eaten the same day ye offer it, and on the morrow: and if ought remain until the third day, it shall be burnt in the fire.

verses.text_plain: And if it be eaten at all on the third day, it is abominable; it shall not be accepted.
verses.verse_html: 7And if it be eaten at all on the third day, it is abominable; it shall not be accepted.

verses.text_plain: Therefore every one that eateth it shall bear his iniquity, because he hath profaned the hallowed thing of the Lord: and that soul shall be cut off from among his people.
verses.verse_html: 8Therefore every one that eateth it shall bear his iniquity, because he hath profaned the hallowed thing of the Lord: and that soul shall be cut off from among his people.

verses.text_plain: And when ye reap the harvest of your land, thou shalt not wholly reap the corners of thy field, neither shalt thou gather the gleanings of thy harvest.
verses.verse_html: 9And when ye reap the harvest of your land, thou shalt not wholly reap the corners of thy field, neither shalt thou gather the gleanings of thy harvest.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt not glean thy vineyard, neither shalt thou gather every grape of thy vineyard; thou shalt leave them for the poor and stranger: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 10And thou shalt not glean thy vineyard, neither shalt thou gather every grape of thy vineyard; thou shalt leave them for the poor and stranger: I am the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall not steal, neither deal falsely, neither lie one to another.
verses.verse_html: 11Ye shall not steal, neither deal falsely, neither lie one to another.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall not swear by my name falsely, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 12And ye shall not swear by my name falsely, neither shalt thou profane the name of thy God: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not defraud thy neighbour, neither rob him: the wages of him that is hired shall not abide with thee all night until the morning.
verses.verse_html: 13Thou shalt not defraud thy neighbour, neither rob him: the wages of him that is hired shall not abide with thee all night until the morning.

tokens.text: with thee all night until the morning

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not curse the deaf, nor put a stumblingblock before the blind, but shalt fear thy God: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 14Thou shalt not curse the deaf, nor put a stumblingblock before the blind, but shalt fear thy God: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall do no unrighteousness in judgment: thou shalt not respect the person of the poor, nor honour the person of the mighty: but in righteousness shalt thou judge thy neighbour.
verses.verse_html: 15Ye shall do no unrighteousness in judgment: thou shalt not respect the person of the poor, nor honour the person of the mighty: but in righteousness shalt thou judge thy neighbour.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not go up and down as a talebearer among thy people: neither shalt thou stand against the blood of thy neighbour: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 16Thou shalt not go up and down as a talebearer among thy people: neither shalt thou stand against the blood of thy neighbour: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not hate thy brother in thine heart: thou shalt in any wise rebuke thy neighbour, and not suffer sin upon him.
verses.verse_html:
17Thou shalt not hate thy brother in thine heart: thou shalt in any wise rebuke thy neighbour, and not suffer sin upon him.
 and: or, that thou bear not sin for him

footnotes.body_text: and: or, that thou bear not sin for him
footnotes.body_html: and: or, that thou bear not sin for him

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not avenge, nor bear any grudge against the children of thy people, but thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 18Thou shalt not avenge, nor bear any grudge against the children of thy people, but thou shalt love thy neighbour as thyself: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall keep my statutes. Thou shalt not let thy cattle gender with a diverse kind: thou shalt not sow thy field with mingled seed: neither shall a garment mingled of linen and woollen come upon thee.
verses.verse_html: 19Ye shall keep my statutes. Thou shalt not let thy cattle gender with a diverse kind: thou shalt not sow thy field with mingled seed: neither shall a garment mingled of linen and woollen come upon thee.

tokens.text: Thou shalt not let thy cattle

verses.text_plain: And whosoever lieth carnally with a woman, that is a bondmaid, betrothed to an husband, and not at all redeemed, nor freedom given her; she shall be scourged; they shall not be put to death, because she was not free.
verses.verse_html:
20And whosoever lieth carnally with a woman, that is a bondmaid, betrothed to an husband, and not at all redeemed, nor freedom given her; she shall be scourged; they shall not be put to death, because she was not free.
 betrothed: or, abused by any: Heb. reproached by (or, for) man
 ,
 she shall: or, they, etc: Heb. there shall be a scourging

tokens.text: they shall not be put to death

footnotes.body_text: betrothed: or, abused by any: Heb. reproached by (or, for) man
footnotes.body_html: betrothed: or, abused by any: Heb. reproached by (or, for) man

footnotes.body_text: she shall: or, they, etc: Heb. there shall be a scourging
footnotes.body_html: she shall: or, they, etc: Heb. there shall be a scourging

verses.text_plain: And he shall bring his trespass offering unto the Lord, unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, even a ram for a trespass offering.
verses.verse_html: 21And he shall bring his trespass offering unto the Lord, unto the door of the tabernacle of the congregation, even a ram for a trespass offering.

verses.text_plain: And the priest shall make an atonement for him with the ram of the trespass offering before the Lord for his sin which he hath done: and the sin which he hath done shall be forgiven him.
verses.verse_html: 22And the priest shall make an atonement for him with the ram of the trespass offering before the Lord for his sin which he hath done: and the sin which he hath done shall be forgiven him.

verses.text_plain: And when ye shall come into the land, and shall have planted all manner of trees for food, then ye shall count the fruit thereof as uncircumcised: three years shall it be as uncircumcised unto you: it shall not be eaten of.
verses.verse_html: 23And when ye shall come into the land, and shall have planted all manner of trees for food, then ye shall count the fruit thereof as uncircumcised: three years shall it be as uncircumcised unto you: it shall not be eaten of.

tokens.text: unto you: it shall not be eaten

verses.text_plain: But in the fourth year all the fruit thereof shall be holy to praise the Lord withal.
verses.verse_html:
24But in the fourth year all the fruit thereof shall be holy to praise the Lord withal.
 holy: Heb. holiness of praises to the Lord

footnotes.body_text: holy: Heb. holiness of praises to the Lord
footnotes.body_html: holy: Heb. holiness of praises to the Lord

verses.text_plain: And in the fifth year shall ye eat of the fruit thereof, that it may yield unto you the increase thereof: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 25And in the fifth year shall ye eat of the fruit thereof, that it may yield unto you the increase thereof: I am the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall not eat any thing with the blood: neither shall ye use enchantment, nor observe times.
verses.verse_html: 26Ye shall not eat any thing with the blood: neither shall ye use enchantment, nor observe times.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall not round the corners of your heads, neither shalt thou mar the corners of thy beard.
verses.verse_html: 27Ye shall not round the corners of your heads, neither shalt thou mar the corners of thy beard.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall not make any cuttings in your flesh for the dead, nor print any marks upon you: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 28Ye shall not make any cuttings in your flesh for the dead, nor print any marks upon you: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Do not prostitute thy daughter, to cause her to be a whore; lest the land fall to whoredom, and the land become full of wickedness.
verses.verse_html:
29Do not prostitute thy daughter, to cause her to be a whore; lest the land fall to whoredom, and the land become full of wickedness.
 prostitute: Heb. profane

tokens.text: to cause her to be a whore

verses.text_plain: Ye shall keep my sabbaths, and reverence my sanctuary: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 30Ye shall keep my sabbaths, and reverence my sanctuary: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: Regard not them that have familiar spirits, neither seek after wizards, to be defiled by them: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 31Regard not them that have familiar spirits, neither seek after wizards, to be defiled by them: I am the Lord your God.

tokens.text: not them that have familiar spirits

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt rise up before the hoary head, and honour the face of the old man, and fear thy God: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 32Thou shalt rise up before the hoary head, and honour the face of the old man, and fear thy God: I am the Lord.

verses.text_plain: And if a stranger sojourn with thee in your land, ye shall not vex him.
verses.verse_html:
33And if a stranger sojourn with thee in your land, ye shall not vex him.
 vex: or, oppress

verses.text_plain: But the stranger that dwelleth with you shall be unto you as one born among you, and thou shalt love him as thyself; for ye were strangers in the land of Egypt: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 34But the stranger that dwelleth with you shall be unto you as one born among you, and thou shalt love him as thyself; for ye were strangers in the land of Egypt: I am the Lord your God.

tokens.text: with you shall be unto you as one born
among you, and thou shalt love
him as thyself; for ye were strangers

verses.text_plain: Ye shall do no unrighteousness in judgment, in meteyard, in weight, or in measure.
verses.verse_html: 35Ye shall do no unrighteousness in judgment, in meteyard, in weight, or in measure.

verses.text_plain: Just balances, just weights, a just ephah, and a just hin, shall ye have: I am the Lord your God, which brought you out of the land of Egypt.
verses.verse_html:
36Just balances, just weights, a just ephah, and a just hin, shall ye have: I am the Lord your God, which brought you out of the land of Egypt.
 weights: Heb. stones

verses.text_plain: Therefore shall ye observe all my statutes, and all my judgments, and do them: I am the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 37Therefore shall ye observe all my statutes, and all my judgments, and do them: I am the Lord.
